text: After several tense days of vote-counting in a handful of battlegrounds, Joe Biden achieved a decades-long ambition in his third attempt at the presidency.Mr. Biden’s victory amounted to a repudiation of President Trump by millions of voters exhausted with his divisive conduct and chaotic administration.The result also provided a history-making moment for Kamala Harris, who became the first woman — and first woman of color — on a winning presidential ticket.

These are five takeaways from President-elect Joe Biden’s victory speech.
Joe Biden has spent his career devoted to institutions and relationships. And those are the tools he will rely on to govern a fractured nation.
People don’t usually have spontaneous dance parties for Joe Biden. But defeating President Trump changed all that.
What happens now? Listen to a special roundtable with our reporters on The Daily.
Vice President-elect Harris, the daughter of an Indian mother and Jamaican father, has risen higher in the country’s leadership than any woman ever before her.
Some see Kamala Harris’s ascension as a reminder to Black girls that anything is possible.
Aides said the president had no plans to immediately deliver the kind of concession speech that has become traditional in past elections.
As President Trump refused to concede defeat on Saturday, top Republican congressional leaders followed suit.
Four days after election night, news networks waited until a fresh batch of Pennsylvania votes allowed them to project a winner.
Neither of Georgia’s Republican senators drew a majority on Election Day, sending both of their races to January runoffs.
The host Dave Chappelle, who also hosted the first episode after the 2016 election, urged Americans to “find a way to forgive each other.”
Nick Rocco, a passionate Trump follower in liberal Massachusetts, slowly realized the results weren’t going his way.
Scenes of jubilation spread minutes after news outlets had called the election for Joe Biden. They lasted into the night.

These are five takeaways from President-elect Joe Biden’s victory speech.
People don’t usually have spontaneous dance parties for Joe Biden. But defeating President Trump changed all that.
In his first hours as president, Joe Biden plans to establish a pandemic testing board and announce that the U.S. will rejoin the Paris climate accord.
Aides said President Trump had no plans to immediately deliver the kind of concession speech that has become traditional.
Joe Biden has a narrow lead in Georgia, and two runoffs there will determine control of the Senate. Are the Democrats’ gains an aberration or a shift?
As eastern counties shifted left, Joe Biden was propelled into victory in a state that President Trump narrowly won in 2016.
President Trump’s charges of fraud have riled supporters in Pennsylvania, which mirrors a divided nation.
Joe Biden’s victory was particularly sweet for supporters in the “blue wall.”
America’s pandemic election was a remarkable, unlikely feat — conducted under assault from its president.
About a fifth of all voters said the protests were the single most important factor in their decision at the ballot box, according to a new survey.
Some see Kamala Harris’s ascension as a reminder to Black girls that anything is possible.
With control of the Senate unclear, liberal Democrats are trying to figure out how to achieve their policy goals through the White House.
Alec Baldwin as the president mourned the results, and the host Dave Chappelle urged Americans to “find a way to forgive each other.”
